Class DFAChecker

java.lang.Object
  java.awt.Component
      java.awt.Container
          java.awt.Window
              java.awt.Frame
                  DFAChecker
All Implemented Interfaces:
ActionListener, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, EventListener, Accessible
public class DFAChecker
extends Frame
implements ActionListener

This application will take in a binary string of any random length and run it through a simulated DFA machine. The Graphical User Interface allows for the user to input the states in the graph along with their respective destinations via user input in the text boxes. The program will assert if the proper destination was reached and show the patht the binary string created when traveling throughout the DFA.

Author:
Joseph E. Cenci February 28th, 2017. @ Joseph E. Cenci 2017

endState

public int endState(String testString)
Method endState - Runs the binary string input through the list of DFA states and returns the final state the string has terminated on. If a kill state is reached, indicated by a -1, the method ends with a return of -1.

Parameters:
testString - The binary string that is input by the user to be broken down and passed through the DFA.
Returns:
int The state number the program terminated on.

validString

public boolean validString()
Method validString - Checks to see that all possiblly reached states have their own respective outward edges. This prevents errors being thrown from having out of bounds exceptions when checking for the next state.

Returns:
True if all states have been satisfied, False if not.
